physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Thickened nuchal translucency of 3.4 mm, absence of nasal bones, poor ossifications in the cranium and vertebrae.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Fetal ultrasound at 21 weeks 4 days showed mild improvement in cranium ossification with hypo-mineralization, persistent lack of nasal bones, poorly ossified vertebrae, femur and humerus lengths below the tenth percentile, and bowing of the tibia and fibula.
